5.2 Integrated Case Study: Autonomous Maritime Vessel

System Overview: Unmanned cargo vessel with hybrid diesel-electric propulsion.

Integrated Hybrid Intelligence System:

**1. Optimization Subsystem (Voyage Planning & Energy Management):

· Multi-objective GA optimizes route considering:
  · Weather forecasts (fuzzy uncertainty handling)
  · Fuel consumption (neural network predictor)
  · Schedule constraints
  · Security risk zones (from security subsystem)
· Fuzzy Logic Controller manages power distribution between diesel generators and batteries

**2. Maintenance Subsystem (Condition-Based Maintenance):

· CNN + LSTM predicts engine RUL from vibration and exhaust gas data
· Fuzzy Health Manager prioritizes maintenance actions:
  ```
  IF engine_health < 0.3 AND security_threat_level = LOW 
  AND port_distance < 200nm THEN schedule_maintenance = IMMEDIATE
  ```
· CBR retrieves similar maintenance scenarios from fleet database

**3. Security Subsystem (Cyber-Physical Protection):

· Anomaly Detection: Autoencoder detects unusual network traffic patterns
· Physical Security: Computer vision (YOLO + CNN) identifies approaching vessels
· Fuzzy Threat Assessor: Evaluates intent of approaching vessels
· Autonomous Response: RL agent chooses optimal evasion/maneuver patterns

Cross-Subsystem Synergies:

· Maintenance → Security: Engine health status influences evasion capability
· Security → Optimization: Threat zones modify optimal routing
· Optimization → Maintenance: Voyage plan affects engine wear prediction
· All → Digital Twin: Continuous simulation for what-if analysis and training

Results: 22% fuel savings, 45% reduction in unplanned maintenance, successful defense against simulated cyber-physical attacks.

